# WHAT IT IS
#   EdgeMesh is the KubeEdge subproject that provides edge-
#   native service discovery and a libp2p-based overlay network
#   between cloud and edge nodes.  Edge clusters typically can't
#   form a flat L3 fabric — different sites live behind
#   different NATs, on different physical networks, sometimes
#   without inbound connectivity — so EdgeMesh uses go-libp2p's
#   DHT + relay-circuit + hole-punch stack to construct an
#   overlay where every node can reach every other node by
#   stable libp2p `PeerID`.  Kubernetes services
#   (`ClusterIP` / headless / NodePort) and gateway routes are
#   plumbed onto that overlay so application Pods on different
#   physical edge sites can address each other by service name
#   regardless of underlying network topology.
#
#   `edgemesh-agent` runs on every node (cloud or edge) and:
#     • joins the libp2p overlay
#     • exposes the local node's services + Pods as overlay-
#       reachable endpoints
#     • implements the dataplane proxy (TCP/UDP forward through
#       the libp2p stream-multiplexer)
#     • participates in the libp2p Kademlia DHT for peer
#       discovery
#
#   `edgemesh-gateway` is the cluster-level ingress that maps
#   external traffic into the libp2p overlay so off-cluster
#   clients can reach edge services without becoming overlay
#   participants themselves.
#
