# AXIS / CORPUS POSITION
#   Direct dependency on `github.com/libp2p/go-libp2p v0.28.2`
#   + `github.com/libp2p/go-libp2p-kad-dht v0.21.0` +
#   `github.com/libp2p/go-msgio v0.3.0` declared in go.mod —
#   `libp2p/go-libp2p` is THE canonical Go libp2p protocol
#   stack maintained by Protocol Labs and the broader libp2p
#   community (libp2p/go-libp2p, 6,500+ stars; the predominant
#   typed Go P2P stack used by Kubo/IPFS, Lotus / Filecoin,
#   Storacha, IceFireDB, Spacemesh, Quorum, Status, taubyte/tau,
#   the Drand randomness beacon, the Eth2 prysm consensus
#   client, and every other production Go P2P application —
#   the conceptual analogue of the n0-computer/iroh stack used
#   for the R989 Axis 100 OPEN leader bump).  go-libp2p exposes
#   the typed `libp2p.New(...opts) -> (host.Host, error)`
#   factory with `libp2p.Identity(privkey)` /
#   `libp2p.ListenAddrStrings(addrs...)` /
#   `libp2p.DefaultTransports` / `libp2p.NoTransports` /
#   `libp2p.Transport(quic.NewTransport, ...)` /
#   `libp2p.Security(noise.ID, noise.New)` /
#   `libp2p.Muxer(yamux.ID, yamux.DefaultTransport)` /
#   `libp2p.EnableRelay()` / `libp2p.EnableHolePunching()` /
#   `libp2p.EnableNATService()` / `libp2p.NATPortMap()` /
#   `libp2p.EnableAutoRelayWithStaticRelays(staticRelays)` /
#   `libp2p.EnableAutoRelayWithPeerSource(peerSource)` /
#   `libp2p.ResourceManager(rm)` /
#   `libp2p.ConnectionGater(gater)` /
#   `libp2p.ConnectionManager(connmgr)` /
#   `libp2p.UserAgent("edgemesh-agent")` constructor options,
#   the typed `host.Host` interface with
#   `host.ID() -> peer.ID` / `host.Addrs() -> []ma.Multiaddr` /
#   `host.Peerstore() -> peerstore.Peerstore` /
#   `host.Network() -> network.Network` /
#   `host.Mux() -> protocol.Switch` /
#   `host.Connect(ctx, peer.AddrInfo)` /
#   `host.SetStreamHandler(protocol.ID, network.StreamHandler)` /
#   `host.SetStreamHandlerMatch(protocol.ID, ...)` /
#   `host.RemoveStreamHandler(protocol.ID)` /
#   `host.NewStream(ctx, peer.ID, protocol.ID...) -> network.Stream`,
#   the typed `peer.ID` / `peer.AddrInfo` / `peer.PeerRecord`
#   / `multiaddr.Multiaddr` / `protocol.ID` /
#   `network.Stream` / `network.Conn` / `network.Network`
#   primitives, the full `kad-dht` Kademlia DHT
#   (`dht.New(ctx, h, dht.Mode(dht.ModeAutoServer),
#   dht.BootstrapPeers(...), dht.ProtocolPrefix(...))` →
#   `*dht.IpfsDHT` with `FindPeer` / `FindProvidersAsync` /
#   `Provide` / `PutValue` / `GetValue` / `Bootstrap`), and
#   the `pubsub` GossipSub mesh
#   (`pubsub.NewGossipSub(ctx, h)` → `*pubsub.PubSub` with
#   typed `Topic` / `Subscription` lifecycle and the message
#   `Validator` hook).  edgemesh's `pkg/tunnel/...` constructs
#   a `libp2p.New` host per `edgemesh-agent` invocation,
#   advertises the `/edgemesh/...` protocol set on the
#   GossipSub mesh, and dials peers found via the Kademlia
#   `Provide` / `FindProvidersAsync` round-trip on the
#   `/edgemesh/dht` protocol prefix.  Verified via:
#     gh api repos/kubeedge/edgemesh/contents/go.mod
#       → module github.com/kubeedge/edgemesh
#       → github.com/libp2p/go-libp2p v0.28.2
